sequenceDiagram
  participant V as Vercel proxy
  participant F as Function App<br/>(vehicleLookup.js)
  participant C as Cosmos<br/>vehicles (PK /placa)
  participant P as Provider (infocar)
  participant I as Infocar API

  alt MISS — cold/expired cache
    V->>F: GET /api/vehicle/plate/{plate}
    F->>C: cache.getCachedByPlate(plate)
    C-->>F: 404 (or non-404 error → fail-open)
    F->>P: lookupByPlate(plate)
    P->>I: POST /Token/GerarToken (cold)
    I-->>P: bearer
    P->>I: GET /CodificacaoFipe/placa/{plate}
    I-->>P: payload
    P-->>F: ProviderResponse
    F-->>V: {cached:false, sources:[...]}
    F-)C: cache.setCachedByPlate (fire-and-forget)
    Note over F,C: wall ~3–5s cold,<br/>~700ms warm
  else HIT — recent doc within TTL 30d
    V->>F: GET /api/vehicle/plate/{plate}
    F->>C: cache.getCachedByPlate(plate)
    C-->>F: doc (point read)
    F-->>V: {cached:true, cached_at, sources:[...]}
    Note over F,C: wall ~500ms<br/>no Infocar call
  else ?fresh=1 — bypass read, still write
    V->>F: GET /api/vehicle/plate/{plate}?fresh=1
    Note over F,C: cache read skipped
    F->>P: lookupByPlate(plate)
    P->>I: token + lookup
    I-->>P: payload
    P-->>F: ProviderResponse
    F-->>V: {cached:false, sources:[...]}
    F-)C: cache.setCachedByPlate (fire-and-forget)
  end

  Note over F,C: Cache writes never fail the response.<br/>Read errors fail-open: log + treat as miss.
